  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTurns out that if you're just importing types, but you use ordinary `import` rather than `import type`, Typescript, well, treats it like an actual import.  We should go over the existing Typescript code and make sure it uses `import type` where possible in order to help keep bundle size down, etc.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.2.3",
